                "type": "section",
                "sections": [],
                "text": "An osyluth practices the craft of torture with the passion of an artist. Their skill draws forth all manner of truths and secrets from their victims, which an osyluth can recall with immaculate precision even centuries later. Over time, osyluths amass sizable collections of information, making them particularly valuable resources to diabolists and other evil spellcasters who crave infernal knowledge. Of course, such conjurers also often employ osyluths for the devils\u2019 cruel talents of interrogation, perpetuating the cycle of spilled blood and stolen secrets.",
